Also, don‚Äôt miss Avatar: The Way of Water back on the big screen in 3D for one week only, starting October 3rd.

The film, which has a screenplay by James Cameron & Rick Jaffa & Amanda Silver, and a story by James Cameron & Rick Jaffa & Amanda Silver & Josh Friedman & Shane Salerno, also stars Sigourney Weaver, Stephen Lang, Oona Chaplin, Cliff Curtis, Joel David Moore, CCH Pounder, Edie Falco, David Thewlis, Jemaine Clement, Giovanni Ribisi, Britain Dalton, Jamie Flatters, Trinity Jo-Li Bliss, Jack Champion, Brendan Cowell, Bailey Bass, Filip Geljo, Duane Evans, Jr., and Kate Winslet.

snippet.title: HAQ | Official Teaser | Yami Gautam Dhar, Emraan Hashmi | Suparn S Varma | In Cinemas 7th Nov
snippet.description:
Shazia Bano takes her husband Abbas to court after he abandons her and their children, sparking a national battle over faith, women‚Äôs rights, and justice. Inspired by the landmark Supreme Court judgement of Mohd. Ahmed Khan vs. Shah Bano Begum. Haq is the story of one woman‚Äôs fight for her rights and justice. 

Releasing in cinemas on 7th November

HAQ is a fictionalized and dramatized version of events stated in the book titled ‚ÄòBano: Bharat ki Beti‚Äô written¬†by¬†Jigna¬†Vora.

What to expect: Slow and low conditions are expected, typical of this venue. Early on, the new ball will skid onto the bat, allowing for fluent shot-making. However, after the first 10 overs, batting will become tougher, with timing and placement more challenging. Batters often resort to high-risk shots to hit sixes, creating both scoring chances and wicket-taking opportunities.

Team news:

India:

Injuries/unavailability: No reported injuries in the Indian camp.

Tactics & Matchups: India are likely to rest Jasprit Bumrah for this game, which could open the door for Harshit Rana‚Äîoffering both pace and added batting depth. Jitesh Sharma might also get a chance, having consistently impressed during net sessions. A key battle will be in the middle overs against Wanindu Hasaranga, who has been highly economical so far, conceding no more than 27 runs in any Asia Cup match.

Probable XI: Abhishek Sharma, Shubman Gill, Suryakumar Yadav (c), Tilak Varma, Sanju Samson (wk)/Jitesh Sharma (wk), Hardik Pandya, Shivam Dube, Axar Patel, Kuldeep Yadav/Arshdeep Singh, Jasprit Bumrah/Harshit Rana, Varun Chakaravarthy

Sri Lanka:

Injuries/unavailability: All players are available for this match.

Tactics & Matchups: India's spin attack, conceding less than 6 runs per over in this Asia Cup, will pose a tough challenge for Sri Lanka‚Äôs middle order, which has struggled for form. In their last game, Sri Lanka brought in Chamika Karunaratne and Maheesh Theekshana, but the move didn‚Äôt pay off. They are likely to revert to their previous combination and bring in an additional batter.

Probable XI: Pathum Nissanka, Kusal Mendis (wk), Kamil Mishara, Kusal Perera, Charith Asalanka (c), Dasun Shanaka, Kamindu Mendis, Wanindu Hasaranga, Dunith Wellalage, Dushmantha Chameera, Nuwan Thushara

Skandamata Mantra | ‡§∏‡•ç‡§ï‡§®‡•ç‡§¶‡§Æ‡§æ‡§§‡§æ ‡§Æ‡§Ç‡§§‡•ç‡§∞ | Navdurga Day 5

Skandamata, the fifth form of Maa Durga, is worshipped on the fifth day of Navratri. She is the mother of Lord Kartikeya (Skanda) and is a symbol of motherly love, compassion, and strength. Riding on a lion and holding her son in her lap, Skandamata blesses her devotees with prosperity, wisdom, and salvation.

Chanting the Skandamata Mantra removes obstacles, grants peace of mind, and fulfills the wishes of her devotees.

üå∫ Benefits of chanting Skandamata Mantra:
Brings harmony and prosperity in family life.
Bestows wisdom, knowledge, and spiritual progress.
Grants strength and courage to overcome challenges.

üôè Listen to this powerful mantra with devotion during Navratri or in daily prayers to receive Maa Skandamata‚Äôs divine blessings.

‚ú® May Goddess Skandamata shower love, peace, and happiness upon you and your family.

Skandamata, the fifth form of Maa Durga, is worshipped on the fifth day of Navratri. She is the mother of Lord Kartikeya (Skanda) and is a symbol of motherly love, compassion, and strength. Riding on a lion and holding her son in her lap, Skandamata blesses her devotees with prosperity, wisdom, and salvation.

Chanting the Skandamata Mantra removes obstacles, grants peace of mind, and fulfills the wishes of her devotees.

Teams

Preview

India are yet to put together a perfect performance in this year‚Äôs Asia Cup, but such is the depth and talent of this new-look Men in Blue side that, even without hitting top gear, they‚Äôve looked a cut above the rest.

Unbeaten so far, India became the first team to seal a spot in the final after a convincing win over Sri Lanka in their last outing. They now face Sri Lanka in what is effectively a dead rubber, a chance to fine-tune their plans ahead of the much-anticipated final against India on Sunday.

snippet.description:
Junglee Music Tamil unveils the full video "Vazhiyiraen", the latest single from the highly anticipated film Madharaasi, written and directed by A.R. Murugadoss. Featuring the charismatic Sivakarthikeyan and the graceful Rukmini Vasanth, Vazhiyiraen stands out as an emotionally rich and visually stunning track that beautifully captures themes of love, hope, and longing. With Anirudh Ravichander‚Äôs heartfelt composition and soul-touching vocals, the song resonates deeply, offering a cinematic musical experience that lingers long after it ends.

Set against picturesque visuals and brought to life by the tender chemistry between the lead pair, Vazhiyiraen is quickly becoming a fan favorite among Tamil romantic songs 2025. Perfect for those who enjoy melodious love songs, Anirudh hits, and lyrical storytelling, this track adds emotional depth to the Madharaasi soundtrack. Don't miss this musical gem that's already trending under #VazhiyiraenSong, a must-watch for fans of Sivakarthikeyan movies, AR Murugadoss direction, and Tamil film music at its finest.

snippet.title: Qainaat | Bir Singh | Nirvair Pannu | Tanu Grewal ‚ÄúSoohe Ve Cheere Waleya‚Äù | Jass Records
snippet.description:
QAINAAT is a heartfelt song written and sung by BIR SINGH, with music produced by BEAT
MINISTER. The song beautifully captures the emotions of love through soulful and poetic
expressions. In the lyrics, a boy describes his beloved as the center of his universe. He
cherishes the tender moment of her resting on his shoulder, a symbol of peace, completeness,
and eternal bond.

The artist expresses that when he saw the girl, he felt truly complete, his heart overflowing
with emotions to the point of tears. He weaves this feeling into words, comparing her beauty
to the moon illuminating the dark night. Through its touching imagery, Qainaat becomes
more than a song‚Äîit is a poetic journey of love, longing, and the purity of heartfelt emotion.


Song : Qainaat 

Singer/Lyrics/Composer : Bir Singh
Music : Beat Minister
Mix and Master Sameer Charegaonkar

‡§®‡§µ‡§∞‡§æ‡§§‡•ç‡§∞‡§ø ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡§æ‡§Ç‡§ö‡§µ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§¶‡§ø‡§® ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Ç ‡§∏‡•ç‡§ï‡§Ç‡§¶ ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§§‡§æ ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ï‡§•‡§æ | Navratri Day 5 - Maa skandmata ki katha 

Best wishes to everyone on the fifth day of Navratri. Skandamata is worshiped on the fifth day of Navratri. Maa #Skandamata‚Äã is the fifth incarnation of Goddess Durga. The word Skandmata is made up of two words - Skanda and Mata. Skanda is another name for Lord Kartikeya, Kartikeya is the son of Bholenath and Parvati mother and brother of Ganesha. Mata means mother and thus Skandamata means mother of Kartikeya. Hence Skandamata is a form of Maa Parvati.
Goddess Durga has four arms in the form of Skandamata. She is holding Kartikeya (Skanda) in one hand, holds a lotus in the other and third hand and blesses the devotees with the fourth hand. She rides a lion and sits on a lotus, which is why she is also called Padmasana. Karthikeya is known as Murugan in South India. He is the commander-in-chief of the army of gods.  Worshiping Maa Skandamata awakens the Vishuddhi Chakra, through which effect one attains the attainment of speech, increases in age and becomes a scholar. The worship of Skandmata leads to the knowledge of sixteen arts and sixteen figures. There is an interesting story of the birth of Karthikeya.Let us now hear the story of Mother Skanda Mata and know that the puja vidhi of Mother Skanda Mata. The story of Skanda Mata reveals who the Goddess Skanda Mata is. How did the goddess get this name of Skanda Mata? In this video Skanda Mata Aarti, Skanda Mata Mantra, Skanda Mata Kavach and Skanda Mata Stotram are also shown

‡§®‡§µ‡§∞‡§æ‡§§‡•ç‡§∞‡§ø ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡§æ‡§Ç‡§ö‡§µ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§¶‡§ø‡§® ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Ç ‡§∏‡•ç‡§ï‡§Ç‡§¶ ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§§‡§æ ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ï‡§•‡§æ | Navratri Day 5 - Maa skandmata ki katha 

Best wishes to everyone on the fifth day of Navratri. Skandamata is worshiped on the fifth day of Navratri. Maa #Skandamata‚Äã is the fifth incarnation of Goddess Durga. The word Skandmata is made up of two words - Skanda and Mata. Skanda is another name for Lord Kartikeya, Kartikeya is the son of Bholenath and Parvati mother and brother of Ganesha. Mata means mother and thus Skandamata means mother of Kartikeya. Hence Skandamata is a form of Maa Parvati.
Goddess Durga has four arms in the form of Skandamata. She is holding Kartikeya (Skanda) in one hand, holds a lotus in the other and third hand and blesses the devotees with the fourth hand. She rides a lion and sits on a lotus, which is why she is also called Padmasana. Karthikeya is known as Murugan in South India. He is the commander-in-chief of the army of gods.  Worshiping Maa Skandamata awakens the Vishuddhi Chakra, through which effect one attains the attainment of speech, increases in age and becomes a scholar. The worship of Skandmata leads to the knowledge of sixteen arts and sixteen figures. There is an interesting story of the birth of Karthikeya.Let us now hear the story of Mother Skanda Mata and know that the puja vidhi of Mother Skanda Mata. The story of Skanda Mata reveals who the Goddess Skanda Mata is. How did the goddess get this name of Skanda Mata? In this video Skanda Mata Aarti, Skanda Mata Mantra, Skanda Mata Kavach and Skanda Mata Stotram are also shown
